// Hand-maintained: NOT generated by mmtorust.
//
// Rust port of `OMCompiler/Compiler/BackEnd/HpcOmBenchmarkExt.mo`, whose
// bodies are all `external "C"` wrappers over
// `OMCompiler/Compiler/runtime/HpcOmBenchmarkExt.cpp`. mmtorust can only
// emit `todo!()` for `external "C"` bodies, so this module is hand-written
// and `HpcOmBenchmarkExt` is listed in `HANDWRITTEN_TOP_PACKAGES`
// (mmtorust/src/codegen.rs) to skip its codegen.
//
// The C++ file consists of:
//  * `requiredTimeForOp` / `requiredTimeForComm` — once real micro-benchmarks
//    (RDTSC timing loops), long since commented out upstream; both return
//    hardcoded `(m, n)` cost-model coefficients for `y = m*x + n`.
//  * `readCalcTimesFromXml` / `readCalcTimesFromJson` — readers for the
//    `<prefix>_prof.xml` / `<prefix>_prof.json` profiling files written by
//    the simulation runtime (`SimulationRuntime/c/simulation/modelinfo.c`)
//    when a model is simulated with profiling enabled. Upstream parses them
//    with expat / cJSON; here with `roxmltree` / `serde_json`.
//
// Both readers return a *flat* `list<Real>`: for each profiled block, the
// triple (count, time, id) is prepended in block order, so the consumer
// (`HpcOmBenchmark.expandCalcTimes`, pattern `numOfCalcs::calcTimeSum::eqIdx`)
// sees the blocks in reverse document order. That shape is load-bearing —
// keep it in sync with `HpcOmBenchmark.mo`.

